originalText.text:
I shall tell a tale of three times I tried to get a correct breakfast sandwich order. Time number one:

I order a egg bacon and Swiss on a roll. They make it, but I end up with American "cheese".

The second time I order, I order an egg bacon and cheese not caring what type, but I ask them to add hot sauce. No hot sauce on sandwich.

The 3rd and last time I order an egg bacon cheese and hot sauce. Three times they asked me if I want a bacon cheese and hot sauce, and I reply affirmatively each time.

There was no egg on the sandwich.

So yeah, I'm done there.

originalText.text: It's a standard Spanish Bodega that used to have some pretty serviceable Dominican food basics in the back. Lately, every time I go back there I find dried out Caribbean breakfast  food items sitting in the steam table. Because everything else looked not so good, I took some chicken soup. How bad can Dominican chicken soup be? The soup in the picture was dreadful because they used yesterday's broth to float new pieces of fairly hard chicken (not cooked enough) and hard, freshly sliced hunks of celery that you see there. It was gross and I threw it all away. This place, unfortunately, has seen better days like many Harlem Dominican spots. Bad cooking by untalented cooks seems to be the thing these days uptown.

Yesterday I did witness money concerning greed, please make sure you come in with someone that can count money if you have trouble with this.
It's best to pay with cash over card. Buy a simple sandwich they will mess up. The bread is cheap very thin I also had too much mayo in my sandwich, if they messed up on my cut and mayo I wouldn't expect them to be able to keep to your order so yes keep it simple. Other than that it is still convenient for other items.

originalText.text: Their food is overpriced for what they sell and the amount given. Also, they give people the wrong food orders! If you do buy from there, always be sure to check your bag and make sure everything is there before you leave. Would not recommend.
